 "description": "Undead — not Lycanthropes, whatever older texts say. Direct sunlight, running water, or a wooden stake through the heart kills them; nothing else does. They are hit only as Spectres are, and even then loss of all hit points merely drives them into gaseous form. Their blow drains two life energy levels; they regenerate 3 hit points per turn the moment they are struck. They summon aid at will — 10-100 rats or bats, or 3-18 wolves — and shift at will into a great bat or into vapor. Their gaze Charms men-types (as Charm Person, victim's save at −2). Garlic, a mirror's face, or a cross strongly presented drives them back; by day they must lie in a coffin floored with the soil of their homeland. Their victims rise as Vampires in thrall to their maker.",
 "special_notes": [
